<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Latin_profanity&amp;action=edit&amp;section=59" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> See, e.g., Jean-Benoît Nadeau, Julie Barlow, <i>The Story of French</i>, p. 233 (Macmillan, 2006: <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0312341830" class="internal">ISBN 0312341830</a>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780312341831" class="internal">ISBN 9780312341831</a>)</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Cicero, <i>Epistolae ad Familiares</i>, 9.22</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> Raffaele Garrucci, <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=U8EYAAAAIAAJ&amp;pg=PA318" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=U8EYAAAAIAAJ&amp;pg=PA318" rel="nofollow"><i>Sylloge inscriptionum Latinarum aevi Romanae rei publicae...</i></a>, Paravia 1875, p. 318.</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> Antonio Varone, <i>Erotica Pompeiana: Love Inscriptions on the Walls of Pompeii</i>, 2002, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/888265124X" class="internal">ISBN 888265124X</a>, p. 147.</li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> Adams, p. 110.</li>
